I"â<p>Neural workspace theory argues that attention is a <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/evolution-is-like-buying-a-suit">selective process</a> involving <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/consciousness-as-latent-representation-store-is-consonant-with-experiential-insights">multiple competing stimuli</a>. In this <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/neural-dynamicity-has-evolutionary-advantages">evolutionary process</a>, firing synchrony is posited to signal <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/abundance-signals-fitness">fitness</a>, as the selection process is <a class="internal-link" href="/secondbrain/representationism-in-cognition-is-adaptationism-in-evolution">pressured by relevance</a>.</p>
